## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-260"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A>操作必须在事务内才能成功。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-260">The <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A> operation must be within a transaction to succeed.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-261">只需<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A>调用`BFILE` , 就会<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile>将对象与另一个文件相关联, 但不会更新 Oracle 表。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-261">Simply calling <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A> on a `BFILE` associates the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> object with a different file, but does not update the Oracle table.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-262">若要在调用<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A>后更新 Oracle 表, 必须`Update`调用的方法<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataAdapter> , 然后提交事务。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-262">To update the Oracle table after calling <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A>, you must call the `Update` method of the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataAdapter> and then commit the transaction.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-263"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.DirectoryName%2A>检索或<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A> `BFILE` <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile>属性后, <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile>它们将缓存在对象中, 并不受任何克隆对象的调用或数据库中的任何更改的影响。 <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.FileName%2A></span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-263">Once you retrieve the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.DirectoryName%2A> or <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.FileName%2A> property, they are cached in the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> object and are unaffected by any cloned <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> objects' calls to <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A>, or by any changes to the `BFILE` in the database.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-264">换言之, 它们可能不表示服务器中`BFILE`对象的实际值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-264">In other words, they might not represent the actual values of the `BFILE` object in the server.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-265">此外, 检索任一属性 (<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.DirectoryName%2A>或<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.FileName%2A>) 都将导致从<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile>服务器中检索这两个属性值并将其缓存在对象中。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-265">Furthermore, retrieving either property (<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.DirectoryName%2A> or <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.FileName%2A>) causes both property values to be retrieved from the server and cached in the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> object.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-266">下面C#的示例在 Oracle 表中假定此架构:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-266">The following C# example assumes this schema in an Oracle table:</span></span>  
  
```  
(col1 number, col2 BFILE)  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="da7a5-267">该示例演示如何使用<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A> <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A>和方法来访问对象。<xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile></span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="da7a5-267">The example demonstrates using the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.SetFileName%2A>, <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> and <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A> methods to access an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> object.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
byte[] buffer = new byte[100];  
OracleDataReader dataReader = command.ExecuteReader();  
using (dataReader) {  
    if (dataReader.Read()) {  
        OracleBFile BFile = dataReader.GetOracleBFile(1);  
        using (BFile) {  
            BFile.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin);  
            BFile.Read(buffer, 0, 100);  
            command.Transaction = connection.BeginTransaction();  
            BFile.SetFileName("TESTDIR", "File1.jpg");  
            BFile.Read(buffer, 0, 100);  
        }  
    }  
}  
